olive oil
6 Mini Flour Tortillas
1 onion
1 carrot
½ tin black beans
1 avocado
½ packet tomato paste
1 packet pulled beef
½ cup water
20 g butter
1 bag salad leaves
1 packet sour cream
1 sachet Louisiana spice blend

• Preheat oven to 200°C/180°C fan-forced. Cut mini flour tortillas into quarters.
• Divide tortilla quarters between two lined oven trays (don’t worry if they overlap).
• Drizzle with olive oil and season with salt. Toss to coat, spread out evenly, then bake until lightly golden and crispy, 8-10 minutes.

TIP: Keep an eye on them. You want them crisp, but not burnt!

• Meanwhile, thinly slice red onion. Grate carrot. Drain and rinse black beans (see ingredients). Slice avocado in half, scoop out the flesh and roughly chop.
• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over a medium-high heat. Cook onion and carrot until softened, 3-5 minutes.
• Add Louisiana spice blend and tomato paste (see ingredients) and cook until fragrant, 1 minute.

• Add pulled beef, black beans and the water to the pan and cook, breaking up beef with a spoon, until slightly thickened, 2-3 minutes.
• Add the butter and salad leaves, then stir until wilted, 1 minute.

• Divide American pulled beef and black bean chilli between bowls.
• Top with sour cream and avocado. Serve with homemade tortilla chips.